  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b89\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0b9e\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9 \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4 12 \u0b85\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0b89\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc0\u0bb1\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b92\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Adjournment of hearings on 12 fundamental rights violation petitions related to Easter Sunday attacks",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "The lawyers appearing on behalf of former President Maithripala Sirisena have requested that in the 12 fundamental rights violation petitions filed against the present President Ranil Wickremesinghe, one of the defendants, who have failed to prevent the 21/4 Resurrection Sunday terrorist attacks despite having sufficient intelligence information Argued in court.",
        "These fundamental rights violation petitions were heard by Chief Justice Jayantha Jayasuriya, Justices Bhuvanega Aluvihara, L.T.P.Tehithenia, Murtu Fernando, S. Durairaja, A.H.M.D. Nawaz and Shiran Gunaratna were taken for questioning yesterday (27) before a panel of seven judges.",
        "At the same time, President's lawyer Faiser Mustapha, who appeared in the forum on behalf of former President Maithripala Sirisena, put forward this argument.",
        "When the case came up for hearing yesterday (26), a fundamental objection was raised by senior counsel Suren Fernando on behalf of one of the defendants, former Prime Minister and current President Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "Lawyer Suren Fernando stated that while his service recipient is currently sworn in as the President, no case can be filed against him as per Article 35 of the Constitution, which is his constitutional right to leave.",
        "Another defendant, former President Maithripala Sirisena's counsel, President's Counsel Faizer Mustapha, strongly opposed the said basic objection and put forward arguments today (27).",
        "President's lawyer Faizer Mustafa stated that the argument put forward by his lawyers that they cannot proceed with these fundamental rights violation petitions against the current president is baseless.",
        "'Presidential leave is irrelevant to this case. There is no bar to proceed with this case against the current President Ranil Wickremesinghe.",
        "Ranil Wickremesinghe's official activities during his tenure as Prime Minister will not be covered by the leave that comes with him as President.",
        "Therefore, an order should be issued that the case against Ranil Wickramasinghe can be continued.' As requested by President's Counsel Faizer Mustafa.",
        "Following this, the hearings on the petitions have been adjourned until the 2nd of August, on which day President Ranil Wickremesinghe's lawyers will present their arguments in this regard."
      ],
